isn't my proposal strictly better here, you can pre-compute the epoch transition without relying on the payload itself which means you can run it earlier in the previous slot (as soon as you see the beacon block and are confident it won't be reorged)

while in the current spec you would have to wait until the payload arrives or you have enough PTC votes (>50%) to be confident that the next block (when calling `get_head`) will be build on top of the post payload state (FULL) and not the post block state (EMPTY)

so pratically, if you wanna be prepared for both cases, don't you even need to pre-compute two epoch transition, one based on `payload_states[parent]` and another based on `block_states[parent]`
